<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/688</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Secretary of Commerce</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jones</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-11">August 11, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Dean</hi>: Your letter of the 1st, file TA
                            611.2531/681, has had consideration.</p>
                        <pb facs="0610" n="600" xml:id="pg_600"/>
                        <p>The matter of an excise tax on copper from Chile or the amount of such
                            excise tax is one for the President and the Secretary to determine.
                            There probably should be some excise tax, although 4 cents appears quite
                            high.</p>
                        <p>I shall be glad to discuss the matter further if you wish.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jesse H. Jones</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>